{"id": 7851, "source": "pestle", "subject": "chemistry", "course": null, "level": "SL", "paper": "1", "year": "2020", "session": "20N", "subtopic": "4-5-metallic-bonding", "title": "20N.1.SL.TZ0.12", "topic_id": "4", "source_url": "https://pestle.pages.dev/app/", "question_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p><span class=\"fontstyle0\">Which series shows the correct order of metallic bond strength from strongest to weakest?</span></p>\n<p>A.  <math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Na</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mi>Rb</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mi>Mg</mi></math></p>\n<p>B.  <math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Mg</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mi>Rb</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mi>Na</mi></math></p>\n<p>C.  <math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Rb</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mi>Na</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mi>Mg</mi></math></p>\n<p>D.  <math class=\"wrs_chemistry\" xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>Mg</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mi>Na</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mi mathvariant=\"normal\">K</mi><mo>&gt;</mo><mi>Rb</mi></math></p>\n</div>", "solution_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>D</p>\n</div>", "examiners_html": "<div class=\"question\">\n<p>A small majority of candidates could identify the relative strength of metallic bonding amongst group 1 and 2 metals.</p>\n</div>"}